According to the results of a recent research, religious belief would work as a kind of analgesic, which would have already helped to make the death of Catholic martyrs more sustainable.
The British daily Telegraph published an article according to which researchers at the University of Oxford realized an interesting experience by analyzing how much faith in God could influence tolerance to the pain of the human being.
As part of this experience for the least odd, 12 Catholic believers and so many atheists were subjected to electroshocks, while each of them observed a painting representing the Virgin Mary.
